title: Commemorative Oak at Sutter's Fort State Historic Park
description: This oak was planted in 1939 to commemorate the 80th anniversary the city of Sacramento's foundation. It was provided by the city of Kandern in Baden-Württemberg, Germany, John Sutter’s birthplace. Folks looking into it determined that it is not native to southern Germany, and is a Quercus petraea (sessile oak). Though it doesn't produce acorns it otherwise seems to like its environment. citation: www.internationaloaksociety.org/content/sutters-forts-ses...
label: Original
